        },
        "text": "In addition, the need for sector-specific legislation concerning consumer protection should be carefully assessed, especially when it leads to regulatory inconsistencies and interpretative challenges. For example, the Electricity Market Directive (EU) 2019/944 includes too detailed requirements regarding complex billing information and summaries of the key contractual conditions, which have proven difficult to implement in practice and may create confusion for both consumers and businesses.",
